data.summary:
Data Analyst/Scientist with experience in the public and private sector.
Data development, data manipulation, investigating data quality, investigating internal data and data from external suppliers.
ETL, Statistical analysis, modelling (GLM, propensity, general linear models, multivariate analysis, cluster analysis), dissemination and reporting. Communicating results to stakeholders.

Experienced using a number of statistical and mathematical packages: 
- R, S-PLUS, Python (numpy, pandas, sklearn);
- SAS-base, SAS-SQL, SAS-macros, PROC R, SAS-hash tables (SAS desktop, SAS Enterprise Guide), developed and presented SAS tutorials for different levels of users;
- SQL, NoSQL;
- Experience with using version control applications (Git and Subversion).
and also:
- Power BI, Tableau;
- Jupyter Notebook, Orange, KNIME;
- Hadoop, Hive, Pig, Spark, Zeppelin, Hortonworks;
- WPS, EMBLEM, Radar, Minitab, Genstat, WinBUGS, OpenBUGS, Mathcad, MATLAB;
- Visual Basic (VB) for MS Excel;
- MS Excel (Certification in MS Excel 2010, 20 October 2013, score: 3.88, percentile: scored higher than 97% of previous examinees, no. 4 top scorer UK)
- MS Word, MS PowerPoint, MS Access, MS Outlook, Lotus notes.
